    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of evergreen flowering plant. Formerly cultivated for a red dye, alizarin, that was obtained from the ground-up roots of these plants. Also used for medicinal purposes and as food plant for the larvae of the Hummingbird hawk moth and other species.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
